  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">At Shari's we use two types of marketing to attract new or existing customers: corporate marketing and local store marketing. Corporate marketing is mandatory, meaning the entire company participates. These marketing activities include newspaper and television advertising and promotions, coupons and discounts, and programs; such as table tents and pie of the month. Local marketing is handled at the store or district level and is designed and implemented by the store management staff. Local marketing is more individual and usually reflects the personality of the store location and staff. Typically, there are three types of local marketing: holidays and events, community involvement and guest and employee interaction (or FUN!).</td>
  </tr>
